\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, any request entering the queue can immediately be serviced (
\begin_inset Formula $P=0$
\end_inset

).
 Finally, we note that the case of zero offered traffic 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 corresponds to a queue that receives no requests (
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 is not well-defined).
 In light of this, we assume the following for the remainder of this work:
