\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "lem:newtons_method_for_convex_functions"

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $g\colon I\rightarrow\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 be a convex differentiable function on an interval 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 with at least one root there.
 Then, given 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{0}\in I$
\end_inset

, the sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ x_{n}\right\} $
\end_inset

 defined by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x_{n+1}=x_{n}-g\left(x_{n}\right)/g^{\prime}\left(x_{n}\right)\text{ for }n>0
\]

\end_inset

converges to a root of 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 provided that 
\begin_inset Formula $g^{\prime}\left(x_{0}\right)\neq1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}\in I$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

